Subject: Blowing Blue

From experience with Chev v/8s, the first puff of blue was an indicator that
something in the valve stem "sealing" system was worn, and when motor was off,
fluid crept down valve shaft to burn at next ignition phase, and escape out
the tailpipe. FFT
Sid
